      • ROUTE_CRITERIA_AVOID_VIGNETTE

        public static final int ROUTE_CRITERIA_AVOID_VIGNETTE
        Constant to specify that the route find avoid vignettes Vignette is simply a road toll subscription, or a pass. Used primarily in Europe for certain roads (all highways) in lieu of physical toll booths. Drivers there instead buy this pass on an annual basis, which grants them road access privileges.

    • Method Detail

      • requestTravelTimes

        public final ICancellable requestTravelTimes(RouteManager.TravelTimeOptions options,
                              RouteManager.ITravelTimeResponseListener listener)
        Request travel times for a route.
        Parameters:
        options - Contains the route ID, the travel time count, and the travel time interval as mandatory parameters, and the departure time and arrival time as optional parameters.
        listener - The listener that will receive the response.
        Returns:
        An instance of ICancellable so that the request can be cancelled.
        Throws:
        RouteManager.RouteManagerException - when either options or listener is null.

        Parameters:
        options - Information about what travel times to calculate.
        listener - The listener that will receive the response.

      • requestRoutes

        public final ICancellable requestRoutes(RouteManager.RouteOptions options,
                         RouteManager.IRouteResponseListener listener)
        Takes a set of waypoints and calculates one or more routes from the first waypoint to the last waypoint, passing through other optional waypoints in turn.
        Parameters:
        options - Information on what routes to return.
        listener - The listener that will receive the response.
        Returns:
        An instance of ICancellable so that the request can be cancelled.
        Throws:
        RouteManager.RouteManagerException - when either options or listener is null.
